\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section introduces the design and internals of the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pkg{showtext}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 package.
 To describe the mechanism behind that, it would be helpful to first have
 a brief introduction to the graphics device in R.
 A graphics device is like an engine that defines a number of basic operations
 in creating an image, i.e.
 draw a straight line, create a rectangle, render text, etc.
 Plotting functions in R combine these basic operations to accomplish more
 sophisticated tasks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each of these operations is defined by a C-level function, which can be
 named as a 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
dfn{device procedure}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 Below lists some device procedures that are related to text rendering:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
code{metricInfo()}
\end_layout

\end_inset

: compute the metric information (height, width, depth, etc.) of a given
 character
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
code{strWidth()}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
code{strWidthUTF8()}
\end_layout

\end_inset

: return the width of a given string
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
code{text()}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
code{textUTF8()}
\end_layout

\end_inset

: draw the text at a give location
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In general, every graphics device needs to implement its own device procedures
 including the items listed above.
 This means that different devices will have different interfaces to select
 fonts for use, which is why there is hardly a universal text rendering
 approach.
\end_layout

